frameDefinitions: A Surrenderer is compelled to transfer a Theme to a Recipient.
A Donor transfers a Theme from a Donor to a Recipient.
This frame involves a Donor transferring a Theme to a Recipient.
A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
This frame describes a Theme losing its autonomy and perhaps sustaining material damage as the result of a successful invasion on the behalf of a Conqueror.
frameExamples: Shortly after the boy <t>surrendered</t> the gun, the three remaining warriors made a rush for liberty.
By the 1920s a characteristic book <t>had</t> black and white photographic illustrations only .
The Spaniards <t>conquered</t> the Incas with both the Cross and the arquebus
